1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Did you know that in Morocco it is common to exchange a small gift when meeting somebody for the first time?

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:11,000
In Japan you must always commit suicide to avoid embarrassment.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:17,000
In Italy you must always wash your hands after going to the bathroom.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,000
This is considered to be polite.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Why are you telling us this?

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:25,000
I am jetting off on an international business trip.

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Where are you going?

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,000
To Canada.

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Where is it?

10
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Canada.

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,000
Okay.

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:36,000
My boss is sending me abroad to do a presentation to an international client.

13
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
And I have always been intrigued by all things international.

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
The women, the pancakes, the man of mystery.

15
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
In England they say hi.

16
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
In China they say hi-ya.

17
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,000
In France the women are sexy.

18
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
In Latin America the women are spicy.

19
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:58,000
In Germany the women are robust and huge.

20
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Where are you getting your information?

21
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:03,000
From the information superhighway and from movies.

22
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Gung Ho, European Vacation, Notting Hill, Under the Tuscan Sky.

23
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Michael, where in Canada do you need to know all this?

24
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Good question.

25
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:20,000
I will be flying from the Scranton International Airport to the Winnipeg International Airport.

26
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Where people from all over the world will see me not just as Michael Scott business man but as Michael Scott ambassador.

27
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Then you should probably know that in Canada it is a sign of respect to offer a bottle of Vermont maple syrup.

28
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Really?

29
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Okay.

30
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Wallace did a terrible thing to Michael.

31
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:44,000
He transferred Holly to another branch, destroyed their relationship, and then to make it all better he chooses Michael to go on a business trip.

32
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Classic abusive parent.

33
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Here Michael, take this drug to numb the pain that I inflicted on you when I was high.

34
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
And the drug in all this?

35
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Status.

36
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Meredith, I would like you to pretend that you are from Abu Dhabi.

37
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Hello.

38
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,000
I am ashamed at your naked face.

39
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,000
I must cover it with my jacket.

40
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,000
You are now sexy in your culture.

41
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:50,000
T minus 6.5 days.

42
00:02:50,000 --> 00:03:06,000
One more week.

43
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Pam comes back from New York next week and everyone here has just been so excited for me and involved and intrusive and weird.

44
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,000
One more week.

45
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Do you have your passport?

46
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,000
I have my passport.

47
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Got your per diem?

48
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
I have my per diem.

49
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,000
I already know what I am going to spend this on.

50
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
I am going to buy a sweater.

51
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Michael, that is for your food.

52
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Well, I will just use different money for that.

53
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
I was happy to send Michael on this trip.

54
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:45,000
He has been feeling pretty down since we had to transfer Holly up to New Hampshire.

55
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,000
But this little perk really seemed to turn him around.

56
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:55,000
And it is pretty tough to find somebody who wants to go up to Winnipeg mid-November.

57
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:03,000
And business class air, like a five-star hotel in the sky, nothing but the best, actually better than a five-star hotel.

58
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:11,000
You get a big cushy seat and you sit in a row of people and to eat whatever the mind can imagine.

59
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:16,000
I think I am going to have a filet with mushroom sauce.

60
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:19,000
Well, I am just glad you are happy because you know I felt bad.

61
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Well, that is all in the past.

62
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:26,000
And in terms of nightlife, when you get there, just ask the concierge.

63
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
They have one of those?

64
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Let's do this.

65
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Wait, why do you need three suitcases?

66
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Two are empty for souvenirs.

67
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,000
You have your money belt?

68
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
I do. It is right here.

69
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Oh, no, no, no, no. You want to wear that puppy right up on the breastbone like a bra.

70
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,000
No, I do not want to wear a bra.
